# Compiler Source Contract

Same module shape as generated code, with compiler-specific imports.

## Module shape
- **Leaf** `src/.../name.py` → exactly one top-level `def name(...)`.
- **Composite package** `src/.../pkg/__init__.py` → exactly one top-level `def pkg(...)`; orchestrate via `from .child import child`.
- **Namespace package** → empty `__init__.py` (docstring only); import leaf modules directly.

## Imports (compiler)
| Kind | Allowed |
|------|---------|
| leaf `.py` | stdlib, `from src.<pkg>.<leaf> import <leaf>` |
| composite `__init__.py` | `from .<child> import <child>`, `from src.<pkg>.<leaf> import <leaf>` |
| forbidden | cross-sibling hacks, multiple top-level functions/classes |

## Exemptions (infrastructure only)
- `src/errors.py` — exception types
- `src/import_rules.py` — AST verifier used by emitter
- `src/schema/engine.py` — `ValidationResult` dataclass

## Project layout
```
io/input/          jobs in
io/schema/         JSON schemas + type registry
io/output/         generated workplace + shared + algorithm + logs
config/            llm + app config
src/               compiler (this rule)
src/algorithm/     algorithm registry + layout bootstrap
run.py             entry → src.src()
tools/             verify_src_contract.py
```

## Output layout
```
io/output/
  workplace/     generated job packages
  shared/        reusable leaf implementations
  algorithm/     fixed-task algorithms (distribution+business pinned; index.json)
  memory/        leaf recall index
  logs/
```

## Private logic
Prefer nested functions inside the single public function before adding new leaf files.
